<FIRST>r a PM-People-Clark     05-27 0163</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-People-Clark,0168</SECOND>
<HEAD>Eastside Principal Joe Clark to Have Open-Heart Surgery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEWARK, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bat-and-bullhorn-wielding high school
principal Joe Clark, who gained national attention because of his
disciplinary tactics, is scheduled to undergo open-heart surgery.
   Clark, principal of Eastside High School in Paterson and the
subject of the movie ``Lean On Me,'' was admitted Wednesday to Beth
Israel Hospital in Newark, said Vincent Fusco, his personal manager.
   ``He's been run-down,'' Fusco said Friday. ``He had pneumonia a
couple of weeks ago. He was out of school for five or six days.''
   The principal, who made the cover of Time magazine because of
the renown and criticism he received for his ``no-nonsense''
educational approach, said from his fifth-floor hospital bed that
he entered the hospital to ``ascertain for a very high temperature
and to diagnose heart irregularities.''
   ``I am in good spirits,'' Clark said.
   Neither hospital spokesman Tom Casey nor Fusco knew the
specifics of the surgery or when it would be performed.
</TEXT>
