<DATELINE>NEWARK, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Joe Clark, the high school principal known
for his bat-and-bullhorn disciplinary tactics, was hospitalized and
scheduled to undergo open-heart surgery, a spokesman said Friday.
   Clark, principal of Paterson's Eastside High School, was
admitted Wednesday to Beth Israel Hospital in Newark, said Vincent
Fusco, his personal manager.
   ``He's been run-down,'' Fusco said. ``He had pneumonia a couple
of weeks ago. He was out of school for five or six days.''
