<DATELINE>BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A young woman was charged with shooting
and wounding her husband after he allegedly struck her, refused to
turn the radio off and quit singing in bed, police said.
   Sheral Denice Ross, 23, was charged with attempted second-degree
murder after an incident that began Thursday morning with her
