<TEXT>
   The Department of Veterans Affairs says a lack
of funds is forcing it to curtail medical services.
   VA Secretary Edward Derwinski on Friday announced a freeze,
except in emergencies, on accepting new patients with
non-service-connected ailments whose incomes are above certain
limits.
   Rep. G. V. ``Sonny'' Montgomery, D-Miss., chairman of the House
Veterans Affairs Committee, said the new limit essentially would
exclude such veterans with incomes greater than $16,476.
