<HEAD>Small Town Loses Only Police Officer To Burglary Charge</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ARCADE, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The town's only police officer was suspended
without pay after being arrested on a burglary charge.
   ``We thought he was doing an excellent job. The whole town
thought he was doing an excellent job,'' Mayor Gary Black said. ``I
was very shocked. He is a personal friend of mine. We'd done a lot
of things together.''
   Sid Glenn, 24, was arrested Thursday by the Georgia Bureau of
Investigation. Agents searched his home and found items believed to
have been taken in a recent burglary of an Arcade business, bureau
spokesman John Bankhead said.
   Glenn, a patrol officer for the town for about a year, posted
bond Friday and was released from the county jail.
   The north Georgia town, population about 500, used to have two
officers, but the other retired recently, Black said. The Jackson
County Sheriff's Department has agreed to provide an officer until
a replacement can be found.
