<FIRST>r i AM-Israel-Clash     05-27 0321</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Israel-Clash,0333</SECOND>
<HEAD>Soldiers Kill Guerrilla in Firefight on Jordanian Border</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SERGEI SHARGORODSKY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Troops on Saturday shot and killed a guerrilla
who opened fire from across the Jordan-Israel border and wounded
two soldiers, the army command said.
   The attack occurred in a bushy area near the communal settlement
of Hamadiya, 50 miles northeast of Jerusalem, the military command
said.
   An army patrol, ``encountered light weapons fire from east of
the fence'' between Israel and Jordan, and returned fire, the
command said.
   Soldiers searched the area on the Jordanian side of the border
and found the body of a guerrilla dressed in a military-type
uniform and armed with a U.S.-made M-16 assault rifle, an army
spokesman said.
   But in an official broadcast, Jordan said the man may have been
a Jordanian Army soldier, Issa Mahmoud Ahmad, who earlier
disappeared from a border observation post.
   It was the third infiltration or attack from Jordan since May
1988.
   ``We have the impression that this is not a new step or a new
direction,'' Maj. Gen. Amram Mitzna, the head of the Israeli army's
central command, told Israel radio. ``We see that the Jordanians
are making every effort and use all means to keep this border
secure and closed.''
   In previous cases, Mitzna said, guerrillas sneaked by Jordanian
patrols. ``This case is still unclear. We don't know who this man
is, where he left from, who sent him and how he came here.''
   The last raid across the Jordanian border was on March 17 when
two guerrillas ambushed an Israeli frontier patrol, killing one
soldier and wounding another before escaping back to Jordan.
   The Fatah-Uprising group, a Syrian-backed faction of the
Palestine Liberation Organization led by Col. Said Mousa, claimed
responsibility for the attack.
   Three Arab guerrillas infiltrated Israel from Jordan on May 17,
1988, and one was killed in a firefight with Israeli troops. The
others escaped.
</TEXT>
