<HEAD>ETA Claims Car Bombing That Killed Three Policemen</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BILBAO, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Basque separatist organization ETA
claimed responsibility for a car bombing that killed three
policemen and injured five people last week, a newspaper reported
Saturday.
   The Basque daily Egin said ETA sent it a statement also claiming
responsibility for the bombing of a car dealership in Bilbao. That
blast occurred Wednesday, shortly before the car bomb, and
apparently was designed to lure police to the site.
   The car bomb was left in a stolen vehicle parked near the
dealership.
   ETA seeks independence from Spain for the three-province
northern Basque region. In its 21-year campaign of violence, ETA
has claimed responsiblity for killing more than 600 people, mainly
police, military and Civil Guard officers.
   The seven ETA killings this year have occurred since April 4,
when the group broke off three months of peace talks with Spanish
officials and ended a moratorium on attacks on government targets.
