<FIRST>r a AM-People-Shore     05-27 0203</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People-Shore,0210</SECOND>
<HEAD>Town Balks At Naming Street After Dinah Shore</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WINCHESTER, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   City council members have tabled a plan
to rename a street after entertainer Dinah Shore because of public
opposition in her former hometown.
   The city's Merchant Association had wanted to rename a street
between Winchester and Decherd ``Dinah Shore Boulevard,'' in hopes
that the singer's name would attract tourists to this small,
south-central Tennessee town.
   Council members tabled the motion ``under advisement from our
constituents,'' Clerk Jimmy Crownover said. ``Most said they would
want to have a name for the street that had some historical value.''
   Miss Shore, who was taping a television show in Los Angeles
Friday, said she was excited at the thought of a street being named
after her. She grew up in Winchester and later moved to Nashville.
   ``I can't tell you what it would mean to have anything named
after me in Winchester,'' she said.
   ``It makes me want to cry with joy and with a thought of sadness
that my mother and father can't be here to know about it, but I
have a feeling they do.''
   Miss Shore has been invited to a celebration this summer marking
the town's 175th anniversary.
</TEXT>
