<SECOND>AM-BRF--Rampage,0162</SECOND>
<HEAD>40 Youths Rampage Through Greenwich Village; 12 Arrested</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A group of 40 youths rampaged through Greenwich
Village, threatening passers-by with ice picks and razors and
snatching their gold chains, police said Saturday. Twelve people
were arrested.
   The dozen suspects, aged 12 to 18, were arrested about 10 p.m.
Friday, several minutes after they started running wild through the
Washington Square Park area of Manhattan, said police Sgt. Maurice
Howard. The other youths fled.
   Nine were charged as adults with first-degree robbery and
first-degree riot, he said, and three were charged as juveniles.
   One of the nine, a 17-year-old, also was charged with
third-degree sexual abuse for allegedly fondling a woman's breasts.
Another was charged with criminal possession of a dangerous weapon,
an ice pick, and stolen property, a gold chain.
   They were scheduled to be arraigned Sunday.
   Only minor injuries were reported and no one received medical
attention, Howard said.
