<FIRST>r a AM-PigeonPosse     05-27 0177</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Pigeon Posse,0183</SECOND>
<HEAD>Town Blasts Away At Pigeon Population</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RANDOLPH, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A posse armed with shotguns killed about
50 pigeons after changing from lighter ammunition that was ``pretty
much bouncing off'' the birds, police said.
   A one-block area was sealed off and police authorized eight
people to shoot the pigeons, which had been damaging buildings and
posing a health hazard to the community, said Police Chief Elliot
Arens.
   ``Last week we used 8-shot and it was pretty much bouncing off.
We were hitting them and the feathers would fly and they just kept
going,'' Arens said. ``This time we used 4-shot and were knocking
them out pretty good.''
   The group bagged about 50 birds Thursday night. An earlier
outing claimed only 15, Arens said.
   The City Council approved the pigeon shoot, Arens said, after
getting a letter from a doctor and the city attorney confirming the
need to eradicate the birds.
   The pigeon plague descended on this northeastern Nebraska
community after the razing of an old bank building, which they used
as a roost.
</TEXT>
